**Open Sans Font File**
========================
The Open Sans font file is a popular, open-source font family designed by Steve Matteson. It is a humanist sans serif typeface designed for legibility and versatility.

**Font File Details**
--------------------

* Font Name: Open Sans
* Font Type: Sans Serif
* Font Style: Regular, Italic, Bold, Bold Italic
* Font Size: Various sizes available
* Font Format: TrueType (.ttf), OpenType (.otf), Web Open Font Format (.woff), Web Open Font Format 2 (.woff2)

**Using Open Sans in HTML, CSS, and JS**
------------------------------------------

To use the Open Sans font in your web application, you can include the font file in your project and reference it in your CSS styles.

### HTML

```html
<!-- Include the font file in your HTML head section -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap">
```

### CSS

```css
/* Define the font family in your CSS styles */
body {
  font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
}

/* Use the font family in your CSS classes */
.header {
  font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: bold;
}

/* Use the font family in your CSS IDs */
#title {
  font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 36px;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

### JS

```javascript
// Use the font family in your JavaScript code
const title = document.getElementById('title');
title.style.fontFamily = 'Open Sans, sans-serif';
title.style.fontSize = '36px';
title.style.fontWeight = 'bold';
```

**Using Open Sans in Core PHP**
------------------------------

To use the Open Sans font in your Core PHP application, you can include the font file in your project and reference it in your PHP code.

### PHP

```php
// Define the font family in your PHP variables
$fontFamily = 'Open Sans, sans-serif';

// Use the font family in your PHP code
echo '<p style="font-family: ' . $fontFamily . '; font-size: 18px;">Hello World!</p>';
```

**Using Open Sans in MySQL / MariaDB**
--------------------------------------

To use the Open Sans font in your MySQL / MariaDB database, you can store the font family in a database table and retrieve it in your PHP code.

### SQL

```sql
-- Create a table to store font families
CREATE TABLE font_families (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  font_family VARCHAR(255)
);

-- Insert the Open Sans font family into the table
INSERT INTO font_families (id, font_family) VALUES (1, 'Open Sans, sans-serif');
```

### PHP

```php
// Connect to the database
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Retrieve the font family from the database
$sql = "SELECT font_family FROM font_families WHERE id = 1";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

// Use the font family in your PHP code
if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
  while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
    $fontFamily = $row['font_family'];
    echo '<p style="font-family: ' . $fontFamily . '; font-size: 18px;">Hello World!</p>';
  }
}
```

**Full Logic Example**
---------------------

Here is a full logic example that demonstrates how to use the Open Sans font in a web application:

```php
// Connect to the database
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Retrieve the font family from the database
$sql = "SELECT font_family FROM font_families WHERE id = 1";
$result = $conn->query($sql);

// Use the font family in your PHP code
if ($result->num_rows > 0) {
  while($row = $result->fetch_assoc()) {
    $fontFamily = $row['font_family'];

    // Include the font file in your HTML head section
    echo '<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap">';

    // Define the font family in your CSS styles
    echo '<style>
      body {
        font-family: ' . $fontFamily . ';
      }
    </style>';

    // Use the font family in your HTML content
    echo '<p style="font-family: ' . $fontFamily . '; font-size: 18px;">Hello World!</p>';
  }
}
```

This example demonstrates how to retrieve the Open Sans font family from a database table and use it in your PHP code to generate HTML content with the correct font family.